Package org.cytoscape.dyn.internal.layout.algorithm.standard.force

Interface Summary
Force Force is an interface for force functions in a force simulation.
Integrator Integrator is an interface for numerical integration routines.
 

Class Summary
AbstractForce AbstractForce is an abstract base class for force functions in a force simulation.
DragForce DragForce implements a viscosity/drag force to help stabilize items.
EulerIntegrator EulerIntegrator updates velocity and position data using Euler's Method.
ForceItem ForceItem represents a point particle in a force simulation, maintaining values for mass, forces, velocity, and position.
ForceSimulator ForceSimulator manages a simulation of physical forces acting on bodies.
NBodyForce NBodyForce is a force function which computes an n-body force such as gravity, anti-gravity, or the results of electric charges.
NBodyForce.QuadTreeNode Represents a node in the quadtree.
NBodyForce.QuadTreeNodeFactory Helper class to minimize number of object creations across multiple uses of the quadtree.
RungeKuttaIntegrator RungeKuttaIntegrator updates velocity and position data using the 4th-Order Runge-Kutta method.
Spring Spring represents a spring in a force simulation.
Spring.SpringFactory The SpringFactory is responsible for generating Spring instances and maintaining an object pool of Springs to reduce garbage collection overheads while force simulations are running.
SpringForce SpringForce is the force function that computes the force acting on ForceItems due to a given Spring.
